00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:12.240
at Jehovah's creation.

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:16.559
Although you will be amazed by the magnitude and intricacy of the physical world around

00:00:16.559 --> 00:00:21.039
us, look beyond the awesome material universe.

00:00:21.039 --> 00:00:25.640
See the qualities and personality of our grand creator.

00:00:25.640 --> 00:00:28.440
This will draw you closer to Him.

00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:31.399
Is this difficult to do?

00:00:31.399 --> 00:00:33.079
Not really.

00:00:33.079 --> 00:00:38.399
But it does require that we make a conscious effort to contemplate Jehovah's marvelous creative

00:00:38.399 --> 00:00:39.399
works.

00:00:39.399 --> 00:00:45.679
Now, we warmly invite you to draw closer to your loving Heavenly Father as you observe

00:00:45.679 --> 00:01:16.180
intently some of the wonders of His creation.

00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:24.310
Hey, he's a fast little guy, huh?

00:01:24.310 --> 00:01:25.310
Let's go check this out.

00:01:25.310 --> 00:01:35.969
You know, there's a lot of amazing things to see out here.

00:01:35.969 --> 00:01:38.769
But you can't see them all with your eyes.

00:01:38.769 --> 00:01:39.769
What do you mean?

00:01:39.769 --> 00:01:44.500
Remember, our family study.

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:47.180
You wanted to know how you could really be God's friend.

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:48.180
Really get to know him, remember?

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:49.180
Yeah, I remember.

00:01:49.180 --> 00:01:51.180
You said by studying the Bible.

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:52.180
That's right.

00:01:52.180 --> 00:01:54.579
And studying God's Word is the best way.

00:01:54.579 --> 00:02:00.349
But there's another way.

00:02:00.349 --> 00:02:02.909
Take King David, for example.

00:02:02.909 --> 00:02:05.349
What do you think he saw when he looked at the night sky?

00:02:05.349 --> 00:02:06.349
The stars?

00:02:06.349 --> 00:02:07.349
That's right.

00:02:07.349 --> 00:02:10.030
But he saw more than that.

00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:12.229
He saw Jehovah.

00:02:12.229 --> 00:02:14.229
But how could he see Jehovah in the stars?

00:02:14.270 --> 00:02:16.030
People can see Jehovah.

00:02:16.030 --> 00:02:19.229
David could see who he is, his personality,

00:02:19.229 --> 00:02:22.349
by appreciating the things that he made.

00:02:22.349 --> 00:02:24.949
It helped him to draw close to God.

00:02:24.949 --> 00:02:28.270
You can draw close to Jehovah in the same way,

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:48.500
from looking at what he's made on Earth to the stars above.

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:52.379
He enjoys looking at creation.

00:02:52.379 --> 00:02:55.539
But few realize that they are catching a glimpse

00:02:55.539 --> 00:03:01.370
into the mind and heart of our grand creator.

00:03:01.370 --> 00:03:04.530
Long ago, David learned about Jehovah

00:03:04.530 --> 00:03:07.050
through his inspired word.

00:03:07.050 --> 00:03:13.580
But he also saw and drew close to him through creation.

00:03:13.580 --> 00:03:18.259
When I see your heavens, the works of your fingers,

00:03:18.259 --> 00:03:22.139
the moon, and the stars that you have prepared,

00:03:22.139 --> 00:03:25.900
what is mortal man that you keep him in mind,

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:31.330
and the son of Earthling Man that you take care of him?

00:03:31.330 --> 00:03:33.930
David loved Jehovah

00:03:33.930 --> 00:03:37.530
and saw Jehovah's power, wisdom, and love

00:03:37.530 --> 00:03:41.900
reflected all around him.

00:03:41.900 --> 00:03:44.699
The world we live in today is designed

00:03:44.699 --> 00:03:47.099
to distract us from our creator.

00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:52.539
Do you take time to look beyond the man-made world?

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:57.819
When you do, even something seemingly common

00:03:57.819 --> 00:04:01.539
becomes extraordinary as you open your eyes

00:04:01.539 --> 00:04:03.659
to see the one who made it.

00:04:04.659 --> 00:04:13.229
Life are planet, the starry heavens.

00:04:13.229 --> 00:04:17.230
Looking at these will help you see Jehovah,

00:04:17.230 --> 00:04:19.230
drawing you closer to him.

00:04:19.230 --> 00:04:27.180
At Genesis 155, Jehovah invited Abraham

00:04:27.180 --> 00:04:32.180
to look up to the heavens and count the stars.

00:04:32.180 --> 00:04:36.180
How many stars could he count?

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:43.180
Our Milky Way galaxy contains over 100 billion stars.

00:04:43.180 --> 00:04:48.550
Can we even comprehend such a large number?

00:04:48.550 --> 00:04:52.550
Let's try by comparing each star in our galaxy

00:04:52.550 --> 00:04:54.550
to a page in a book.

00:04:54.550 --> 00:04:58.550
How long would it take to examine those pages?

00:04:58.550 --> 00:05:01.550
At the rate of a page per second,

00:05:01.550 --> 00:05:05.550
it would require over 3,000 years.

00:05:05.550 --> 00:05:08.550
In order to count them in your lifetime,

00:05:08.550 --> 00:05:11.550
you would need to turn about 50 pages per second

00:05:11.550 --> 00:05:14.550
for every moment of your life.

00:05:14.550 --> 00:05:21.269
We lack ability to even count the stars.

00:05:21.269 --> 00:05:25.269
Yet Jehovah knows each one by name.

00:05:25.269 --> 00:05:30.610
Looking beyond our galaxy,

00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:33.610
astronomers are finding that sections of the sky

00:05:33.610 --> 00:05:35.610
appearing nearly empty from Earth

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:39.610
are actually filled with thousands of other galaxies.

00:05:40.610 --> 00:05:45.949
But did Jehovah scatter them randomly?

00:05:45.949 --> 00:05:48.949
Even at this colossal scale,

00:05:48.949 --> 00:05:53.389
elegant organization is seen.

00:05:53.389 --> 00:05:56.389
There is one who is stretching out the heavens

00:05:56.389 --> 00:05:58.389
just as a fine gauze,

00:05:58.389 --> 00:06:03.389
who spreads them out like a tent in which to dwell.

00:06:03.389 --> 00:06:09.389
All of these massive celestial bodies are in constant motion.

00:06:09.389 --> 00:06:12.389
Their precise movements have been likened

00:06:12.389 --> 00:06:15.389
to the choreography of an elaborate ballet.

00:06:15.389 --> 00:06:19.660
Besides their vast numbers,

00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:24.660
the distance between stars is also mind-boggling.

00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:27.660
Let's try to visualize the distance from our sun

00:06:27.660 --> 00:06:31.660
to its nearest neighbor's star, Proxima Centauri.

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:37.740
Imagine that we could shrink our Milky Way galaxy

00:06:37.740 --> 00:06:41.740
so that our sun was roughly the size of a soccer ball,

00:06:41.740 --> 00:06:44.740
located near New York City.

00:06:44.740 --> 00:06:47.740
On this scale, Proxima Centauri

00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:51.740
would be almost 4,000 miles away in Paris, France,

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:55.740
a little smaller than a golf ball.

00:06:55.740 --> 00:07:03.850
Really, the sun is almost 25 trillion miles away

00:07:03.850 --> 00:07:09.410
from its nearest neighbor's star.

00:07:09.410 --> 00:07:11.410
We only have to look at the stars

00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:14.410
to be filled with awe for Jehovah.

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:17.410
Yet, as the book of Job describes,

00:07:17.410 --> 00:07:22.410
what we see are only the fringes of his ways.

00:07:22.410 --> 00:07:27.300
When the prophet Isaiah looked at the stars,

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:31.300
he perceived Jehovah's qualities.

00:07:31.300 --> 00:07:34.300
Raise your eyes high up and see

00:07:34.300 --> 00:07:38.300
who has created these things.

00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:41.300
It is the one who is bringing forth the army of them

00:07:41.300 --> 00:07:43.300
even by number,

00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:48.300
all of whom he calls, even by name.

00:07:48.300 --> 00:07:52.300
Due to the abundance of dynamic energy,

00:07:52.300 --> 00:07:55.300
he also being vigorous in power,

00:07:55.300 --> 00:07:59.639
not one of them is missing.

